Back at the Tripred base...

Belthassan started to tell the four new members of the Tripredacus.

Belthassan:
Our origins date from before the great wars. Gamma was one of the most 
powerful transformers at the time, but when the time came to choose between 
autobots and decepticons, he chose to leave Cybertron and establish the 
Gammacons. Their goal was to control the violence back on Cybertron. As the 
Autobots and Decepticons became Maximals and Predacons, the Gammacons became 
the Tripredacus. Our goals have changed though, and we have recently 
discovered the power of the matrix, the source of all transformers. We have 
also been reformatting our members because of the higher powers and 
understanding of the matrix it provides. It is a direct link to the Matrix. 
The mission I command here is to gather energy for special research.

Gesper:
By the way, brother, we will have to contact lieutenant Daemos, for we do 
not know where he has established the shrine. I have already sent a message 
to the Hellgate with a relay command.

Astonished at his younger brother's thinking one step ahead of him, 
Belthassan was happy to train him as potential unit leader. If only he could 
be more into combat...

Belthassan:
Well done, Gesper! Tell me should you get a reply.
